# --- Canonical host: force apex (no www) and HTTPS ---
# Netlify normally handles this when the primary domain is set to
# https://jmeszaros.dev in Site settings → Domain management. Keeping these
# explicit rules guarantees the redirect even if a deploy preview / branch
# domain is mis-aliased.
https://www.jmeszaros.dev/*    https://jmeszaros.dev/:splat    301!
http://www.jmeszaros.dev/*     https://jmeszaros.dev/:splat    301!
http://jmeszaros.dev/*         https://jmeszaros.dev/:splat    301!

# IMPORTANT: do NOT add `/en/ → /en` style trailing-slash strip rules here.
# Netlify's internal request normalization will collide with our rule and
# create a redirect loop (`/en` 301→ `/en` 301→ ... — confirmed live with
# `curl -I`). The trailing-slash deduplication is handled at runtime via
# `<link rel="canonical">` in src/components/SEO.jsx, which strips the
# trailing slash before publishing the canonical URL. Google honors that
# canonical signal and merges the duplicates without us forcing 301s.

# --- SPA fallback (must remain last) ---
/*                             /index.html                      200
